Kenneth C. Gilbert is Chairman of the Management Science and Operations Management Program, and an associate professor at The University of Tennessee. He received a B.S. in mathematics from Berea College and an M.S. in mathematics and a Ph.D. in management science from The University of Tennessee. Dr. Gilbert has published in Journal of the Association for Computing Machinery, Journal of the American Society of Civil Engineers, Management Science, Applications of Management Science, IIE Transactions, and Decision Sciences . â€¡ Ruth B. Hofstra is an assistant professor in the Department of Computer Science at Tennessee Technological University. She received B. A. and M. A. degrees in mathematics from Syracuse University, and a Ph.D. in management science from The University of Tennessee. Dr. Hofstra has published in Radiation Research, IIE Transactions, Decision Sciences , and publications of Oak Ridge National Laboratory, Oak Ridge, Tennessee.